The paper deals with signal processing on set functions, which can be seen as a generalization of hypergraphs and cooperative games. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Graph Theory (cs.GT) categories. However, the paper explicitly states that it is not focused on graph signal processing, but rather on a new framework for signal processing on set functions. This suggests that the paper is more likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories, which are more focused on general signal processing and optimization problems. Finally, the paper also mentions applications in submodular function optimization and preference elicitation in auctions, which further supports the idea that it belongs to the Machine Learning or Artificial Intelligence categories.
